messages.text: SafeHaven chat. 02/06/17 3:26 PM.
patientzero is connected.
Hi, Dr. Took.
Dr. Took is connected.
You went offline during our last session, patientzero. I was concerned.
I know. I'm sorry.
I have a few minutes to chat. Can you tell me what happened since we spoke on Thursday?
Nothing happened. I spent the weekend drunk. That's all.
I'm trying to figure all this shit with my brother out.
How are you feeling towards your brother now?
You're asking if I'm still going to kill him, aren't you?
Have you made a plan to do so?
Look, lady. I get that you don't know how it feels but I can't confess.
I can't go to jail, and I can't let my brother murder me.
I have no choice.
You know what?
Getting on here was a stupid fucking idea.
It sounds like you are angry.
You are just full of shrewd observations, aren't you?
I should have gone into psychology.
Oh?
Apparently all you have to do is quote platitudes and say shit like "tell me more about that."
One day at a time, right?
How much did you pay for that PhD?
You should get your money back.
Or did you get that online, too?
Has a therapist said "platitudes" to you before?
Yeah. I was 14 and the school forced me to see a counselor.
Why did the school feel you needed counseling?
Some bitch said I assaulted her.
Did you?
Fuck, does it matter now? I tried to kiss her and she pulled away.
I got angry and shoved her into the lockers.
She cut her head on the metal and bled all over my brand new jeans.
She had to get a few stitches, I guess.
Why did her reaction make you angry?
Because she rejected me.
Had you been rejected before?
Not me.
Who had been rejected?
My mom rejected my dad when I was in elementary school.
She asked for a divorce.
Said she met someone else.
My dad didn't do anything about it, and my brother said it's because he isn't a man.
Did you shove your classmate because you wanted to be seen as a man?
I guess.
By whom?
I needed my brother to like me.
But not your dad?
He wasn't around much. Off drinking.
My brother was like my dad.
That must have been difficult for both of you.
Did you feel guilty about the altercation?
I felt guilty for a while, I guess.
I got suspended at school.
I had to do community service for like six months, and I was on probation, too.
I was a kid though so the record got sealed or whatever.
I see. Do you feel guilty now?
I don't know. My brother helped with that some.
How did he help?
He gave me some beer. He talked to me about it.
And what did he say to you?
He said she asked for it.
That bitches don't get to say no when they look like that.
When they look like what?
Too much makeup, short skirt, heels.
Bitches are sluts.
Let's try to avoid shifting the blame, patientzero.
Why? Did I hit a nerve?
Are you a slut, Hortence?
Are you asking for it, too?
I am concerned that you may soon feel remorseful about your anger at me, too.
I encourage you to think about what you are saying.
I should be angry.
Go on.
I don't know.
I guess it's easier as a man to be angry than afraid.
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry. All I feel is fear.
Fear of your brother?
Yeah.
And fear of getting caught. Fear of getting killed.
Fear of ghosts, of judgment.
Fear of myself.
Why are you afraid of yourself?
Because of the accident.
But not the assault?
I was a dumb kid. It was just a shove.
I guess I still feel a little guilty. But I wouldn't do it again, I don't think.
Do you think you'd drive drunk again?
Or get in the car with an intoxicated driver?
Seriously?
I killed a woman. I left her body in a field.
I was too scared to tell the truth and she's still out there, rotting.
I guess I'm angry at myself.
And your brother?
I don't know.
I think he feels bad about the accident, too.
Why do you think he feels bad?
I heard him crying in the bathroom when we got back to his house.
He was still drinking, yeah, but he felt bad about it, I guess.
But you think he would hurt the brother he acted like a father to?
He's got issues, OK?
I feel his eyes on me sometimes.
Has he threatened you at all?
He doesn't have to. I know he'd do anything to keep from going back to prison.
Like I said, he's got a record.
Is his record for violent offenses?
He's got two DUIs.
Some drug charges. A few assaults.
He thinks I'm going to rat. I know it.
Are you thinking about coming forward?
Of course not. I can't get locked up. I have bad anxiety.
I'm claustrophobic, too. I'd get myself killed.
My brother thinks I'm weak.
Like our dad.
He thinks I'll tell.
I have to stop him.
Do you have a plan, patientzero?
I've thought about it, yeah.
Do you have a weapon?
There's a gun in the house.
Look, none of this matters. I just need you to tell me how to make the guilt stop.
That's why I came here.
I'll deal with my brother.
Killing your brother won't make the guilt stop. In fact, it could probably amplify your sense of shame.
Condemn me if you chooseI do that myselfbut condemn me, and not the path which I am following.
I am not here to condemn, patientzero. I would like to help you.
It's a quote. Tolstoy, actually.
I see. And what do you think about the path you are going down?
I have to protect myself.
There are other ways we can talk about to keep you safe.
No.
I need to know your name.
patientzero?
Are you still connected?
Hello?
patientzero is disconnected.
